observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
Strictly require the preparation of the RSMI by the Supply Officer on a monthly basis and submit the same to the Municipal Accountant;
Direct the Municipal Accountant to:
Prepare and maintain the SLCs for each type of inventory to record the acquisition, issuance and disposal; and
Henceforth, draw a JV for inventory issuances on a monthly basis based on RSMIs that are duly supported with RIS;
Constitute an Inventory Committee who shall   conduct   the   physical count of inventories at least once a year, prepare the RPCI and submit the same to the Audit Team not later than January 31 each year.

We recommended that the:
Supply Officer and other concerned offices prepare and maintain the inventory list of all items received, distributed, and ending balances for proper monitoring;
MDRRM Council prepare a revised/supplemental LDRRMFIP incorporating therein the PPAs for disaster risk reduction and management program that were not embodied in the original plan;
MPDC update/revise the AIP for the inclusion of covid-19 related PPAs;
Municipal Accountant prepare the Report on Sources and Utilization of DRRMF using the format on Annex B as prescribed in COA Circular No. 2012-002 dated September 12, 2012; and
MDRRMO submit the Monthly Report on Sources and Utilization of DRRMF and the Revised LDRRMFIP to COA Office.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the Municipal Accountant and the GAD Focal Person to:
Properly align and include PPAs in the GPB that is gender responsive and will address valid GAD activities;
Provide necessary disclosures in the Notes to Financial Statements as to details of the GAD appropriation during the year and the utilization of the GAD fund.

We recommended to the Municipal Mayor to:
1.	cause the installation of perimeter fence around the disposal site to intensify its physical security and prevent loss or theft of SWM machineries;
2.	cause the creation of peripheral drainage to avoid possible health problems, and;
3.	cause the maintenance of basic record-keeping to keep track of activities necessary for future overall planning purposes and forecasting of site filling.

We recommended to the Municipal Mayor to:
a.	direct the Municipal Treasurer to submit a Status Report on the Revenue Code;
b.	coordinate with the members of the Sangguniang Bayan to look into the possible updating of the Revenue Code based on the report of the Municipal Treasurer.

We recommended to the Municipal Mayor to direct the Municipal Accountant to:

issue demand letters with the signature of the Mayor to the accountable officers concerned;

withhold payment or any amount due to the persons liable to settle said disallowances;

ensure that all employees who are retiring or transferring to other agencies shall first settle the disallowances and charges for which they are liable in accordance with Section 7 of COA Circular No. 2009-006 dated September 15, 2009.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
a.	cause the judicious review of the Memorandum of Agreements of the identified projects for immediate implementation;
b.	require the Bids and Awards Committee to fast-track the procurement process; 
c.	require the Municipal Planning and Development Officer to conduct the programming of development projects judiciously with officials concerned, for the optimum utilization of the funds received.

